.spec/prds/v2/concepts/uc-mol-01-card-listrow.html:1310:    <em>LSContentCard</em> was extracted because every Navigator organism — route results, saved rides, community cards — needed the same <em>surface.card + radius.lg + elevation.2</em> container but with different slot content. Coalescing into one molecule prevents organisms from each choosing their own radii or shadows and guarantees visual consistency across 8+ screens.
.spec/prds/v2/concepts/uc-mol-01-card-listrow.html:1313:    <em>LSListRow</em> enforces the 44pt touch-target floor mandated by both Apple HIG and Material You. The leading/title gap of <em>spacing.3 (8px)</em> was chosen empirically: it gives icon-to-text breathing room without the leading content becoming detached from its label at small viewport widths.
