## Modular Design Analysis (pre-implementation)

### Existing Components Found
- `LSCard` (`android/app/src/main/java/com/laneshadow/ui/atoms/LSCard.kt`) — reusable card surface with token-backed radius/elevation/background semantics.
- `LSText` (`android/app/src/main/java/com/laneshadow/ui/atoms/LSText.kt`) — required typography atom to avoid raw `Text`.
- `LSAvatar` (`android/app/src/main/java/com/laneshadow/ui/atoms/LSAvatar.kt`) — reusable leading avatar for list-row variant.
- `LSIcon` (`android/app/src/main/java/com/laneshadow/ui/atoms/LSIcon.kt`) — reusable trailing/leading icon atom (chevron, utility icons).
- `LSDivider` (`android/app/src/main/java/com/laneshadow/ui/atoms/LSDivider.kt`) — reusable separator atom for row boundaries.
- Existing molecule patterns to follow: `LSRouteAttachmentCard`, `LSFilterChip`, `LSTagPill`, `LSWeatherBadge` for semantics/test/story conventions.

### Reuse Opportunities (Rule of 2 from `dry-methodology`)
- Pattern `MoleculeStoryFrame + story helper` appears in existing molecule stories and will be reused for the 10 new stories.
- Pattern `token-backed spacing via LocalLaneShadowTheme.current.space.*` appears throughout existing molecules and will be reused in both new molecule files.
- Pattern `source-inspection unit tests to enforce atom composition/no raw primitives` appears in current molecule tests and will be reused.

### Unmodular Code Flags
- No unmodular code flags in current in-scope files (`LSContentCard.kt`, `LSListRow.kt`, related tests/stories) because these files do not exist yet.
- Existing out-of-scope files do contain hardcoded dp constants in some molecules/atoms; flagged but not changed due scope constraints.

### Implementation Plan
- Will reuse existing: `LSCard`, `LSText`, `LSAvatar`, `LSIcon`, `LSDivider`, `MoleculeStoryFrame`, story aggregation in `MoleculesStories`.
- Will create new reusable: `LSContentCard` slot-based molecule and `LSListRow` variant-based molecule with semantic keys/tags for deterministic tests.
- Will refactor (flagged only, not fixed unless scope expands): out-of-scope hardcoded size ladders and constants in existing molecules/atoms.
